    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" ns:sid="2047271451424256002" ns:tid="2047271821333442562" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="51">
        <source>Why Is the Battery Energy Insufficient During Morning Peak Hours?</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" ns:sid="2047271451424256003" ns:tid="2047271821333442563" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="36">
        <source>During morning peak hours, electricity demand is high, but PV power generation has not yet reached its peak.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" ns:sid="2047271451424256004" ns:tid="2047271821333442564" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="38">
        <source>Therefore, the system mainly relies on battery discharge to meet load demand.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" ns:sid="2047271451424256005" ns:tid="2047271821333442565" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>Battery policy restrictions</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" ns:sid="2047271451424256006" ns:tid="2047271821333442566" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b151801755374&quot;&gt;</bpt>Incorrect <ph id="f1">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol1891019245456&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784470567.xml#438333&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298266790#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784470567&quot;/&gt;</ph> period settings<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" ns:sid="2047271451424256007" ns:tid="2047271821333442567" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="57">
        <source>If the charging window is not set for nighttime (low electricity price period), the system does not fully charge the battery at night or during low electricity price periods.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" ns:sid="2047271451424256008" ns:tid="2047271821333442568" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>Consequently, the battery's energy reserve is insufficient during peak morning hours.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" ns:sid="2047271451424256009" ns:tid="2047271821333442569" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="43">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b14180135113716&quot;&gt;</bpt>Conservative SOC threshold setting<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" ns:sid="2047271451424256010" ns:tid="2047271821333442570" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="37">
        <source>If the end-of-discharge SOC is set too high (for example, 50%), the available capacity decreases.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" ns:sid="2047271451424256011" ns:tid="2047271821333442571" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="46">
        <source>Consequently, the battery's energy is depleted earlier than expected during peak hours.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" ns:sid="2047271451424256012" ns:tid="2047271821333442572" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b094218107410&quot;&gt;</bpt>Feed-in priority mode<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" ns:sid="2047271451424256013" ns:tid="2047271821333442573" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="44">
        <source>If the mode is set to <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol55241626133415&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207635068172.xml#456541&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207635068172&quot;/&gt;</ph>, PV power is used first to meet home load requirements, and the remaining power is directly sold, affecting the battery's energy reserve.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="13" ns:sid="2047271451424256014" ns:tid="2047271821333442574" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="64">
        <source>Battery capacity and power limits</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14" ns:sid="2047271451424256015" ns:tid="2047271821333442575" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="Onvoldoende capaciteit" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="94">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b71808512377&quot;&gt;</bpt>Insufficient capacity<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match">Onvoldoende capaciteit</target>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15" ns:sid="2047271451424256016" ns:tid="2047271821333442576" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="40">
        <source>If the total battery capacity (kWh) cannot meet the load demand during peak hours, the energy will be quickly depleted.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="16" ns:sid="2047271451424256017" ns:tid="2047271821333442577" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="30">
        <source>For example, if the load is 5 kW for 4 hours during morning peak hours, at least 20 kWh of capacity is required.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="17" ns:sid="2047271451424256018" ns:tid="2047271821333442578" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>If the battery capacity is only 10 kWh, it is insufficient.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="18" ns:sid="2047271451424256019" ns:tid="2047271821333442579" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="Onvoldoende groene stroom" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="79">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b1118145163711&quot;&gt;</bpt>Insufficient power<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match">Onvoldoende groene stroom</target>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="19" ns:sid="2047271451424256020" ns:tid="2047271821333442580" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>If the maximum discharge power (kW) of the battery is lower than the peak load, the system cannot support devices with sudden high-power demands (such as air conditioners starting simultaneously).</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="20" ns:sid="2047271451424256021" ns:tid="2047271821333442581" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="32">
        <source>Load fluctuation and prediction deviation</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="21" ns:sid="2047271451424256022" ns:tid="2047271821333442582" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b18181125123710&quot;&gt;</bpt>Sudden load peak<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="22" ns:sid="2047271451424256023" ns:tid="2047271821333442583" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="27">
        <source>During morning and evening peak hours, home electricity consumption is concentrated (such as cooking and charging).</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="23" ns:sid="2047271451424256024" ns:tid="2047271821333442584" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="35">
        <source>If the load suddenly increases beyond the predicted range, the battery may not be able to respond.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="24" ns:sid="2047271451424256025" ns:tid="2047271821333442585" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="48">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b9181357375&quot;&gt;</bpt>Prediction algorithm error<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="25" ns:sid="2047271451424256026" ns:tid="2047271821333442586" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="57">
        <source>The system schedules energy based on historical electricity consumption data.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="26" ns:sid="2047271451424256027" ns:tid="2047271821333442587" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="28">
        <source>If the actual electricity consumption pattern changes (for example, high-energy-consuming devices are added), the battery's energy reserve may be insufficient.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
